Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine in both serum and blood, indicating significant renal impairment. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, bilirubinuria, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), suggesting possible nephrotic syndrome or severe renal dysfunction. Low urine specific gravity supports impaired concentrating ability. HbA1c is low, excluding chronic hyperglycemia. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation for acute or chronic kidney disease and further assessment for underlying causes.
